Description: Fragment of neck and flattened handle from a Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay accreted. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.102,1. The identity seems good, even if Petrie did not include the clear A in line 1 and seems to have been optimistic at the end of the line. Names, Tachippos and Dorotheos?
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0291)
